Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the sweet potato onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and cooked through,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a
#tight-fitting lid{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and
bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with
the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, boil a half-full #kettle{} for the dressing.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.
Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the
length of the carrot, stopping at the core. Pop the carrot ribbons into a small
#bowl{} with the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar for pickling{1%tsp}. Add a
pinch of @salt{pinch}, mix together, then set aside.

In a small bowl or a #jug{}, combine the @boiled water for the dressing{1%
tbsp}, @miso paste{30%g}, @honey{30%g} and @sambal paste{15%g}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Next, pop a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once
the oil is hot, add the Tenderstem® and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{}, then cover with a #lid{} (or foil) and allow to cook
until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's ready, pour the carrot pickling liquid into the rice and fluff
it up with a #fork{}, then share between your bowls.

Lay the sweet potato onto one half of the rice and spoon over the miso honey
dressing. Add the broccoli to the other side of the bowl, then the pickled
carrot on top.

Scatter over the peanuts to finish. Enjoy!